				p.articletext These two cards work quite well together. Let's walk through it. 

				img(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/v1500588106/kxanim2.gif").center-block

				p.articletext Playing Cut-Rate Mercenary first allows you to draw a card. Afterwards, it continues to sit in play waiting for you to use its MINION skill. Playing Collatoral Damage by itself would deal 4 damage to your opponents and yourself, but since you have a Cut-Rate Mercenary in play you could avoid taking that damage. By choosing to destroy your Cut-Rate Mercenary in reaction to taking damage, Collateral Damage deals 4 damage to your opponents and leaves you unscathed!

				p.articletext Playing Knox will require you to choose which of your MINIONS live and die. Many of Knox's Utilities are very aggressive and Knox can offer lots of support to those MINIONS via his Actions and Feats. Want to help KNOX take over the world? Focus on keeping three Utilities in play at all times in order to keep the pressure up. Draw as many cards as it takes to make secure your ultimate victory!
